**Key Finding — TASK-016 Redaction FAILED** (critical security flaw):
The redaction tool only draws opaque rectangles over content — it does **not** remove the underlying text/image data from the PDF. Users are told content is "permanently removed" when it remains fully extractable. The tester's recommended fix (page-flattening via canvas rasterization) is correct. Added a high-priority monitoring todo to track the fix. No direct intervention needed — PM should re-assign this in the next cycle through normal flow.

**Testing Queue**: 11 items remaining. Tester processed 2 this cycle — at this rate, ~6 more cycles to clear.

**Action Taken**: Updated state.json with new observation, added concern for TASK-016, created monitoring todo #18 for the redaction fix. No system changes needed — observing only.
